    "title": "What will be the security risks if we persist \"e\" as part of schnorr signature=(r,s,e) and get publicKey from signature at verification",
    "body": "Hi folks, \r\n\r\nWe know Unlike `ecrecover`, it is impossible to get to public key given schnorr signature = (r,s) since `rG = sG-eP` . \r\n\r\nSo, would like to understand what are the security risks\r\n\r\nif we say \r\n`signature=F(r,s,e)` \r\nand get to publicKey at the verification? something like this\r\n`P = (rG-sG)/e`",
